###################
# goals
1. capture knowledge / information / processes / etc (not secrets)
2. easily search and find information
  ie. 1. compile a Java application
      2. ssh to box
      3. submit PPM timesheet
      4. configure CUPS printer on windows
3. aggregate sources - multiple references to search across
      1. local
      2. github
4. make utilities portable
  go does this
  shell scripts are slower and not as reliable (especially if they include multiple libraries)
5. capture browser history?

###################
# supported actions
1. create (create new empty reference workspace)
2. index (index workspace(s))
3. search (search workspace(s))
4. git clone (git clone reference workspace)
5. git add
6. git commit
7. git push
8. git pull
9. restore
    restore references from configuration file (operating-systems/freebsd, operating-systems/linux, programming/java)

###################
# supported content
1. plain-text files
2. PDFs
    exported webpages
    need to index these to be able to search through them
    recoll
3. terminal screen captures
4. libreoffice documents
    recoll

###################
# workflow
1. init references
2. add content
  URL
  plain-text description of problem and solution
  PDF export

  ###################
  # alternatives
  1. git hooks with codesearch ()
  2. shell script to standardize reference setup
